questions.statement:
Choose the most suitable option to replace the highlighted part:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
She is &lt;strong&gt;more smarter than&lt;/strong&gt; her peers.

Find the part of the sentence that contains an error:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Neither of the solutions (1)/ appear satisfactory (2)/ to the panel (3)/ reviewing the case. (4)

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;quot;appear&amp;quot; in part 2 is incorrect as the subject &amp;quot;Neither&amp;quot; is singular.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;When the subject is singular, the verb must also be singular to maintain subject-verb agreement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct verb should be &amp;quot;appears&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;appear.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the error is in part 2 of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;Neither of the solutions appears satisfactory to the panel reviewing the case.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 1: &amp;quot;Neither of the solutions&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 3: &amp;quot;to the panel&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 4: &amp;quot;reviewing the case.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
